InsTrack App Privacy Policy
Effective on April 21, 2013; Last Updated on October 23, 2024
1. Introduction
This privacy statement describes how INNOVATTY collects and uses the personal information you
					provide. It also describes the choices available to you regarding our use of your personal
					information and how you can access and update this information.
The terms "INNOVATTY," "we," "us," or "our" refer to INNOVATTY, LLC. The terms "you" or "your" refer
					to the client/customer or users of any interfaces (including, but not limited to, websites and
					emails) provided by INNOVATTY.
2. Collection and Use of Personal Information
We collect the following personal information from you:
Preferences Information
: Product or content interests, communication or marketing
						preferences.
Usage Activity
: Information about how you interact with us, such as content viewed and
						areas of our app visited.
Device Information
: Automatically gathered details about your device, such as type and
						operating system.
We use this information to:
Assess your needs and determine suitable products or services.
Send you push notifications while using our app. You can manage preferences through your device
						or app settings or by contacting us at
contact@innovatty.com
.
Improve our app and marketing efforts.
Conduct research and analysis.
3. Sharing Your Information
We will share your information with third parties only as described in this privacy statement:
Legal Requirements
: To comply with a subpoena, similar legal process, or as required by
						law.
Protection and Safety
: When necessary to protect our rights, ensure your safety or the
						safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.
Business Transfers
: If INNOVATTY is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets,
						you will be notified via email or a prominent notice on our website regarding any change in
						ownership or use of your personal information.
Third-Party Consent
: With your prior consent.
4. Tracking Technologies and Advertising
We partner with third-party ad networks to display advertising on our app or manage advertising on
					other sites. Our ad network partners may use technologies to collect non-personally identifiable
					information about your activities on this and other apps to provide you with targeted advertising
					based on your interests.
5. Security
The security of your personal information is important to us. We follow industry standards to protect
					the information submitted to us, during transmission and once received. However, no method of
					transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. If you have any questions about
					security, contact us at
contact@innovatty.com
.
6. Data Deletion
Your data is primarily stored locally on your device. Some data, such as your account information or preferences, may
					also be stored on our servers for the purpose of providing app functionality. You can permanently delete all local data
					by uninstalling the app from your device. If you wish for us to remove any data stored on our servers, please contact us 
					at
contact@innovatty.com
, and we will process your request accordingly.
7. California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) Rights
Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), residents of California have specific rights
					regarding their personal data:
Access to Information
: Request that we disclose categories and specific details of
						personal information we have collected about you.
Request for Deletion
: Request that we delete any personal information we have collected
						about you.
Opt-Out of Data Sale
: Request that we stop selling your personal data.
If you wish to exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
contact@innovatty.com
. We will respond within 30 days.
8. General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) Rights
We are committed to ensuring that you are fully informed of your rights under the General Data
					Protection Regulation (GDPR). Every user has the following rights:
Right of Access
: Request copies of your personal data. We may charge a small fee for this
						service.
Right to Rectification
: Request corrections to inaccurate information or completion of
						incomplete data.
Right to Erasure
: Request the deletion of personal data.
Right to Restrict Processing
: Request limitations on how your data is processed.
Right to Object
: Object to the processing of your personal data.
Right to Data Portability
: Request that we transfer your personal data to another
						organization or directly to you.
If you wish to exercise these rights, please contact us at
contact@innovatty.com
. We will respond within 30 days.
9. Children's Privacy
Protecting children while using the internet is important to us. We encourage parents and guardians
					to observe, guide, and be involved in their childrenâ€™s online activities.
We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If you
					believe that your child has provided personal information on our website, please contact us at
contact@innovatty.com
immediately. 
					We will take prompt action to remove the information.
10. Notification of Privacy Statement Changes
We may update this privacy statement to reflect changes in our information practices. We encourage
					you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices.
